The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 December is 10,158 (1,175.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 December, there were 593 new confirmed cases (68.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 November, there were 503 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 18% (90 extra cases).
